cc:Work.dc:title: Elvie #017
cc:Work.dc:description:
[Panels 1 & 2: Elvie's friend is speaking to her on the phone]
Friend: Don't you think you're being a bit paranoid with all this encryption nonsense…?
Friend: The government aren't interested in what you had for dinner, or the contents of your shopping list!
[Panel 3: It's revealed that a pair of spies are eavesdropping on Elvie's conversation]
Spy 1: …a bag of prawn crackers, some Garibaldi biscuits, a copy of 'Little Brother' and the latest edition of Linux Voice.
Spy 2: She Sounds like a commie to me. Put her on the watch list.
